sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Doha
sky.tennis.uk.description: Jelena Ostapenko's near seven-year wait to vie for a WTA 1000 title ends in Doha, as the former Grand Slam champion faces 23-year-old American Amanda Anisimova in an unseeded final. (15.02)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Washington
sky.tennis.uk.description: The 2021 US Open finalist Leylah Fernandez competes in her first final in over a year, as the 22-year-old meets Anna Kalinskaya - who eased past Emma Raducanu in the semi-finals. (27.07)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Sao Paulo
sky.tennis.uk.description: A women's singles champion is crowned in the final of the 2025 Sao Paulo Open, a WTA 250 hard-court event held in Brazil. (14.09)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Geneva
sky.tennis.uk.description: A chance for Novak Djokovic to join Jimmy Connors and Roger Federer in winning a 100th tour-level title, as the 38-year-old Serb battles Hubert Hurkacz in the Geneva Open final. (24.05)

sky.tennis.uk.title: Graf v Seles 1995
sky.tennis.uk.description: Two greats of professional tennis contested the 1995 women's singles final at the US Open, as Monica Seles - returning from a terrifying on-court ordeal in 1993 - faced Steffi Graf.

sky.tennis.uk.title: Agassi v Martin 1999
sky.tennis.uk.description: Andre Agassi's 1999 career renaissance concluded with an unforgettable victory at the US Open, earning a fifth Grand Slam title at the expense of his fellow countryman Todd Martin.

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Madrid
sky.tennis.uk.description: Britain's Jack Draper steps on court for the Madrid Open final aiming to lift his second Masters 1000 crown, as the 23-year-old faces 14th seed Casper Ruud for the first time. (04.05)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Dubai
sky.tennis.uk.description: A women's singles champion is crowned in Dubai. Russia's Mirra Andreeva - the youngest-ever WTA finalist - and Denmark's Clara Tauson face off for glory. (22.02)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Monterrey
sky.tennis.uk.description: A women's singles champion is crowned in the final of the Monterrey Open, a WTA Tour 500 event held in Mexico. (23.08)

sky.tennis.uk.title: Best of the US Open 2025
sky.tennis.uk.description: The United States' Taylor Fritz, a runner-up in Flushing the year before and the last American standing, met the 24-time Grand Slam champion Novak Djokovic in the quarter-finals.

sky.tennis.uk.title: Best of the US Open 2025
sky.tennis.uk.description: Home favourite Frances Tiafoe, one of 2024's semi-finalists, entered the third round of the New York Slam to compete with German qualifier Jan-Lennard Struff on Grandstand.

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Rome
sky.tennis.uk.description: World number one Jannik Sinner takes on soon-to-be world number two Carlos Alcaraz in a blockbuster Italian Open final. Between them, the pair have won the last five majors. (18.05)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Indian Wells
sky.tennis.uk.description: Mirra Andreeva meets top seed Aryna Sabalenka in the Indian Wells final. Sabalenka avenged her Australian Open defeat to Keys in the semis, while Andreeva dethroned Swiatek. (16.03)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP/WTA Tour Classic Matches
sky.tennis.uk.description: In a rematch of the 2023 Madrid Open final, world number one Iga Swiatek and defending champion Aryna Sabalenka meet again to determine this year's women's singles champion.

sky.tennis.uk.title: Best Of The ATP Finals
sky.tennis.uk.description: World number one Carlos Alcaraz faces Italy's reigning ATP Finals champion Jannik Sinner in their sixth meeting of the year, marking the finale to the 2025 Tour season in Turin. (16.11)

sky.tennis.uk.title: Best Of The WTA Finals
sky.tennis.uk.description: Aryna Sabalenka and Elena Rybakina - both undefeated in Riyadh - bid to become a first-time WTA Finals champion. This is the 14th meeting between the two, with Sabalenka 8-5 ahead. (08.11)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Indian Wells
sky.tennis.uk.description: Britain's Jack Draper competes in his maiden ATP Masters 1000 final at Indian Wells as the top-10 bound Brit faces Holger Rune. Draper knocked out Carlos Alcaraz in the last four. (16.03)

sky.tennis.uk.title: WTA Final: Osaka
sky.tennis.uk.description: Leylah Fernandez enters her second final of the year as the 2021 US Open finalist gets set to take on talented teenage qualifier Tereza Valentova for the WTA 250 crown in Osaka. (19.10)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP Final: Stuttgart
sky.tennis.uk.description: In a blockbuster Stuttgart final, world number three Alexander Zverev competes for a maiden grass-court title against second seed Taylor Fritz, who leads the head to head 7-5. (15.06)

sky.tennis.uk.title: ATP/WTA Tour Classic Matches

E4Plus1.uk.description: Frankie opens up about her past. Sienna, Dodger and the McQueens step in to help new mum Cleo. And Mercedes and Ste find themselves on a path of self-destruction...

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip from Rude Tube's naughty little sister that features a variety of cats doing strange things, some soldiers stuck in the sand and a dog balancing on a rope.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Peter's: Gordon visits Peter's Italian Restaurant in New York, where the peace of Long Island is shattered by the antics of the volatile Pellegrino family who run the place. (S1 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Mixing Bowl: Bijou New York diner The Mixing Bowl is haemorrhaging money thanks to manager Mike's out of control marketing plans. Can Gordon get things back on track? (S1 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Seascape: Gordon Ramsay visits the Seascape restaurant in the seaside village of Islip, on Long Island in New York, where owner Peter has nearly a million dollars of debt. (S1 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Secret Garden: Gordon Ramsay visits a romantic French restaurant in California, where temperamental chef Michel Bardavid's complicated cuisine is keeping the customers away. (S1 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Middle Earth Paradigm: Penny's Halloween party puts Leonard, Sheldon, Howard and Raj through a demanding new test of their social skills. (S1 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Geology Elevation: Sheldon can't contain his jealousy when he hears that his university colleague, Bert the geologist, has won a prestigious fellowship. (S10 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Property Division Collision: Sheldon, Amy, Leonard and Penny attempt to divide up all their possessions. It doesn't go well. (S10 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Birthday Synchronicity: Sheldon and Amy try to celebrate her birthday with an intimate night at home but are interrupted when Bernadette goes into labour. (S10 Ep11)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Great Festive Bake Off
E4Plus1.uk.description: More merry bakers from Bake Off past - Benjamina, Rav, Rob and Sandy - join Paul, Prue, Noel and Sandi for a winter-wonderland-themed challenge. (Ep2/2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Holiday Summation: After spending Christmas apart, the gang gather at Penny and Leonard's flat and hear about Sheldon and Amy's terrible trip to Texas. (S10 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Romance Recalibration: Penny thinks that Leonard has stopped making an effort in their relationship, so she decides to go away for a spa weekend with Amy. (S10 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Emotion Detection Automation: Sheldon tests a new invention after hearing that it could help him to read people's emotions. Raj seeks dating advice. (S10 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Celebrity D'OHverload
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Springfield Files: Guest starring David Duchovny, Gillian Anderson and Leonard Nimoy. Homer thinks he's seen an alien. This could be a case for Mulder and Scully. (S8 Ep10/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Celebrity D'OHverload
E4Plus1.uk.description: Insane Clown Poppy: Guest starring Drew Barrymore, Stephen King and John Updike. Homer and Bart take Lisa to a book fair, where Krusty meets his long-lost daughter. (S12 Ep3/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Celebrity D'OHverload
E4Plus1.uk.description: Tennis the Menace: Guest starring Serena and Venus Williams, Andre Agassi and Pete Sampras. Homer builds a tennis court in the back garden but Bart's skills annoy him. (S12 Ep12/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Celebrity D'OHverload
E4Plus1.uk.description: Moonshine River: Guest starring Zooey Deschanel, Sarah Michelle Gellar, Anne Hathaway and Natalie Portman. The family travel to New York looking for Bart's long-lost love. (S24 Ep1/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons Celebrity D'OHverload
E4Plus1.uk.description: Marge Gamer: Guest starring Brazilian football legend Ronaldo. Marge gets hooked on an online fantasy game and battles Bart. Lisa gets frustrated playing soccer. (S18 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Bumblebee
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2018) High-octane sci-fi action adventure starring Hailee Steinfeld. When Charlie drives home a clapped-out VW Beetle, she gets more than she bargained for: a huge robotic alien.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Mission: Impossible - Fallout
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2018) Tom Cruise stars in part six of the action-thriller series. His mission: to stop terrorists from getting their hands on nuclear bombs and unleashing global devastation.

Film4.uk.title: Inglourious Basterds
Film4.uk.description: (2009) Quentin Tarantino's World War II action-adventure. Jewish American soldiers go Nazi-hunting in occupied France. With Brad Pitt, Diane Kruger, Christoph Waltz and Michael Fassbender.

Film4.uk.title: Freaky
Film4.uk.description: (2020) Body-swap comedy horror with Vince Vaughn. A girl gets murdered by a serial killer but then wakes up in his body, with only 24 hours to get her own body back!

Film4.uk.title: Deerskin
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Comedy horror. A middle-aged man (Jean Dujardin) buys a deerskin jacket to kick off his post-divorce life. Fine - until the jacket starts talking to him...

Film4.uk.title: Barnacle Bill
Film4.uk.description: (1957) The final Ealing comedy stars Alec Guinness as the latest in a long and distinguished line of sailors, but there's a problem: he suffers from seasickness. So why not buy a pier?

Film4.uk.title: Yesterday's Enemy
Film4.uk.description: (1959) Wartime drama with Stanley Baker. The captain of a British army patrol deciphers secret enemy battle plans, but does so at a great moral cost.

Film4.uk.title: It Should Happen to You
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Judy Holliday stars in this comedy as a smalltown girl who comes to New York and rents a billboard to publicise her name - and soon she's a TV star. With Jack Lemmon.

Film4.uk.title: Mysterious Island
